1
00:00:09,042 --> 00:00:11,810
BY: I've decided to go into showbiz.

2
00:00:11,811 --> 00:00:13,112
Once I make it big,

3
00:00:13,113 --> 00:00:15,080
you'll have a celebrity for a best friend.

4
00:00:15,081 --> 00:00:16,348
I'll definitely save you

5
00:00:16,349 --> 00:00:17,550
a VIP seat at my concerts.

6
00:00:18,985 --> 00:00:20,465
I don't want to just be in the crowd.

7
00:00:20,787 --> 00:00:21,921
With so many fans around,

8
00:00:22,222 --> 00:00:23,723
you'd never even notice me.

9
00:00:24,290 --> 00:00:26,825
Maybe I should just
join the industry too...

10
00:00:26,826 --> 00:00:27,826
as your assistant.

11
00:00:28,795 --> 00:00:30,295
But you're a scholarship student.

12
00:00:30,296 --> 00:00:32,332
It's not like me; I was
never good at school.

13
00:00:33,266 --> 00:00:35,301
I feel like if you really become a star,

14
00:00:35,935 --> 00:00:37,704
we'll end up living in
two different worlds.

15
00:01:01,361 --> 00:01:03,362
You should stop using your burner account

16
00:01:03,363 --> 00:01:05,283
to tell shipping groups
you aren't a good match.

17
00:01:06,699 --> 00:01:08,339
Fine, I'll just use my main account then.

18
00:01:10,370 --> 00:01:11,370
Hey,

19
00:01:11,538 --> 00:01:13,405
about those clips the
advertiser released...

20
00:01:13,406 --> 00:01:15,774
did you make sure to charge them extra?

21
00:01:15,775 --> 00:01:17,576
You've gotta capitalize
on the fame, you know?

22
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:20,046
Take a page out of
Bingchen and Hei Yan's book.

23
00:01:22,682 --> 00:01:23,682
What's wrong with you?

24
00:01:24,050 --> 00:01:25,084
Ever since we wrapped this shoot,

25
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:26,553
you've been so mopey.

26
00:01:27,921 --> 00:01:28,921
What?

27
00:01:29,064 --> 00:01:31,199
Did spending all that time with Hei Yan

28
00:01:31,224 --> 00:01:32,826
give you separation anxiety?

29
00:01:34,828 --> 00:01:35,795
It's fine.

30
00:01:35,796 --> 00:01:38,096
We still have the press conferences,

31
00:01:38,097 --> 00:01:39,598
promotional events, and signings.

32
00:01:39,599 --> 00:01:40,599
I don't want to go.

33
00:01:41,334 --> 00:01:42,494
I don't want to see that guy.

34
00:01:48,508 --> 00:01:49,242
What's the deal?

35
00:01:49,243 --> 00:01:50,543
Do you actually like him?

36
00:01:52,645 --> 00:01:54,080
Like hell I do.

37
00:02:00,053 --> 00:02:01,186
Oh, please.

38
00:02:01,187 --> 00:02:02,688
It's your first time doing a romance,

39
00:02:02,689 --> 00:02:04,729
so it's only natural you
caught some real feelings.

40
00:02:04,891 --> 00:02:06,569
Didn't you say you wanted to be like them?

41
00:02:06,593 --> 00:02:08,394
More fans means more money.

42
00:02:09,496 --> 00:02:11,865
We've already had several
scripts sent our way lately.

43
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:15,000
I just don't like my feelings

44
00:02:15,001 --> 00:02:16,736
being sold like some commodity.

45
00:02:17,537 --> 00:02:18,537
Hey...

46
00:02:18,771 --> 00:02:19,772
I actually meant it.

47
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:21,741
But he was just playing a part.

48
00:02:22,642 --> 00:02:24,202
How can you be so sure it was all fake?

49
00:02:27,514 --> 00:02:28,648
These days,

50
00:02:29,182 --> 00:02:30,616
it's hard to tell who's being sincere

51
00:02:30,617 --> 00:02:32,152
and who's just faking it.

52
00:02:33,019 --> 00:02:34,539
You can't always tell just by looking.

53
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:36,955
If you want to know, just ask.

54
00:02:36,956 --> 00:02:38,036
If you can't get an answer,

55
00:02:38,625 --> 00:02:40,225
then I guess it just wasn't meant to be.
